     stack(int n){
            size = n;
            top = -1;
            int arr[] = new int[size];
        }

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

In the constructor , you are creating a new local variable arr[].
The instance variable is still uninitialised. 
And by default, the value given to it is null.
